    <h3>Eastern Cape Academy of Training and Technology</h3>
    <p>EC Academy is a privately owned and managed institution whose purpose is to empower South African community by providing quality and cost effective courses with skills that can be implemented immediately for business and individual purposes. The academy is situated in Nelson Mandela Bay, Eastern Cape, South Africa. It is 100% black owned and managed.
 
EC Academy was established on 05 January 2006. Within the first six years, the academy trained 300 individuals some of whom have been declared competent in various courses they completed by MICT SETA.
 
 
 	

Under Mr. Zukisani Teyi’s leadership, the academy has continued to grow and gain recognition to the South African community. His National Diploma in Information Technology and extensive experience in the training field has enabled EC Academy to present courses in a manner that is easily understood by students. This is one of the key features that set the academy apart from other institutions.
 
In his strategic planning to build EC Academy as a recognised institution nationally, Mr. Zukisani Teyi and his executive team are planting more campuses throughout the country to ensure that EC Academy's purpose to empower South African community is realised.
 
 
In the year 2010, the academy was awarded full accreditation, with accreditation number ACC/2010/02/790 by MICT SETA (Media, Advertising and ICT Sector Education Training Authority). This accreditation enables the academy to provide quality assured courses, with nationally recognised certificates.

